132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 277
H.P. 181 House of Representatives, January 28, 2025
An Act to Repeal the Law Prohibiting Places of Business from Being
Open to the Public on Sunday
Reference to the Committee on Housing and Economic Development suggested and
ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative MORRIS of Turner.
Cosponsored by Representatives: BAGSHAW of Windham, BOYER of Poland, CHAPMAN
of Auburn, FLYNN of Albion, LIBBY of Auburn, SMITH of Palermo.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 17 MRSA §3202, as amended by PL 1971, c. 334, §1, is repealed.
3 Sec. 2. 17 MRSA §3204, as repealed and replaced by PL 2003, c. 452, Pt. I, §55
4 and affected by Pt. X, §2, is repealed.
5 SUMMARY
66 This bill eliminates the prohibition on a place of business's opening on Sundays and on
77 certain holidays.
